               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370102-name-1020" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-1020" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-1020" type="surname" value="DICKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-1020" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH DICKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Joseph Peppercorn, a cheesemonger. The prisoner came to our shop on the 15th of December, and bought a pennyworth of cheese—I accused him at the door of taking something—he said if he had taken any thing, it was by mistake—I said it could not be</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183701020149"></xptr>
               <p>a mistake—I found this piece of cheese in his bag, which was in his hand—it is my master's—it was agreed for, but the person who bought it had gone to the other counter to buy some more goods.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I was just outside the door, and he called me—I said if I had it, I had put it in by mistake—I had a pound of bread and some other things.</p>
